stoneChat (a caveman peeking at modern technology) is a simple LLM Web Chat, adapted for Windows XP & IE6.

To run it, your device needs a PHP 5.4+ environment (the launcher uses PHP's built-in web server). Get it from:
https://windows.php.net/downloads/releases/archives/

On Windows XP: use php-5.4.45-Win32-VC9-x86.zip -- PHP 5.4 is the last version
to support XP and the first to include the built-in web server. PHP 5.5+ requires
Vista or later. The app code itself is written to run on any PHP 5.x.

As for all the remaining network-related problems, let the program handle them. You will also need stunnel for HTTPS:
https://www.stunnel.org/downloads.html

Download / Clone:
  Clone the repository or download the ZIP.
  Before starting, copy `CONF_SMP.INI` to `CONF.ini` and edit it to set
  your users, model rights, API keys, and providers.

To run directly:
  Double-click RUN.cmd. It performs pre-flight checks and starts
  the local web server. If CONF.ini is missing, RUN.cmd will also create
  one from the CONF_SMP.INI template.

Then visit it in your browser. The default address is:
  http://localhost:9999

You need to edit CONF.ini according to the comments to configure users,
models, providers, and other settings. The launcher validates CONF.ini
before starting so common mistakes are caught early.

stoneChat is open-sourced under WTFPL at:
https://github.com/Water-Run/stoneChat
